OL,6,FPeople are typically infected by
OL,7,Fconsuming contaminated food or drink
OL,8,For by direct contact with contaminated
OL,9,Fanimals.
OL,11,FHSE inspector Francesca Arnold said:
OL,12,F"It is extremely important that
OL,13,Ffarmers understand the risks on their
OL,14,Ffarm, and they should ensure that
OL,15,Fvisitors are protected when inviting
OL,16,Fthe public onto their farms.
OL,18,F"Health risks from contact with the
OL,19,Fanimals need attention and must be
OL,20,Fcontrolled.
